&lt;p&gt;Band 7 Midwife on the Delivery Suite&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flexible employment- potential night only or part time- no less than 23 hours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you have the knowledge and skills to excel in a leadership role?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The applicant will be compassionate, aspirational, resourceful and promote excellence. These trust values are fundamental to the care we provide ensuring evidence based, women centred care and that strives to improve outcomes for women and families accessing the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The applicant with development support will be responsible for the day to day running of the Delivery Suite promoting safety and excellence by being the clinical expert on shift, coordinating care and liaising with the multidisciplinary team. This will require excellent leadership, managerial and communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The applicant would be expected to work flexibly in the Intrapartum team to meet the needs of women in the most appropriate birthing area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The applicant would be required to be innovative and ambitious and lead on a service development project. This would be supported by a named experienced senior midwife and the ward manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Required to complete WAVE Assessment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
